        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=59081&amp;TOPIC_ID=7112&amp;FORUM_ID=3&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=Necromancer+Game+Guides&amp;Topic_Title=Chardok+Info+%2F+Help+please&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         My guild on Emarr successfully raided the royals, and the herbalist several times.  This zone makes for a tough raid, but it is do-able.  Respawn is fast, and you need to be quick, and organized moving from point to point.  I'm not sure if I'm explaining myself well, but let me put it this way - the best advice I can give you is to have someone along on the raid that knows the spawn times, and get yourself (in RL, heh) a good stopwatch/timer.  That one piece of equipment was essential to us on that raid.  </P><P>I'd sure like to go along with you, but heh, I'm lvl 19.  Don't think I'd be much help.  Those raids are some of the best I've ever been involved in.  Oh, one other piece of advice - watch for runners.  We had the king and queen dead, and the last mob with literally a pixel of health managed to get away from us.  We were largely OOM and low on health.  That one escaped runner brought about 700 of his best friends and shirt-tail relatives.  </P><P>Good thing we had a friendly necromancer along.  :D</P><P>Toxi<BR>Lvl 19 Necromancer<BR>Terris Thule</P><P>"Kill" is such a friendly word. - Metallica</P><P>Toxi<BR>Lvl 15 Necromancer<BR>Terris Thule<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
